cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.IR 

This paper discusses the development of a chatbot to improve medication adherence, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and decision support systems (cs.CC). The proposed study also involves tracking and analyzing patient data, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the use of a conversational interface and the focus on patient behavior aligns with the category of computational social systems (cs.CY).
